{"updated_at": "2011-09-28T02:38:47Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-09-28T02:38:47Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2219004", "id": 2219004, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3151", "issue_id": 3151, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/et", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "3787c05a986fc71117e4a83bc47c9637", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/et", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3787c05a986fc71117e4a83bc47c9637?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8257fe03047e82b57406ed493c6e8913.png", "id": 58678, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/events{/privacy}", "login": "et", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/et/followers"}, "body": "Is this really worth it? \r\nObviously we don't want logic in our views, but compare these two:\r\n\r\n`\"<b>#{count}</b> #{pluralize(count, \"dog\", :include_count => false)}\"`\r\n\r\nvs the basic condtion\r\n\r\n`\"<b>#{count}</b> #{count == 1 ? \"dog\" : \"dog\".pluralize}\"`\r\n\r\nThe second version is shorter and expresses the functionality clearly.\r\n\r\nMaybe a better solution would be to just tweak the pluralize String method to take an optional parameter of count.\r\n\r\n`<b>#{count}</b> #{\"dog\".pluralize(count)}`", "_id": {"$oid": "52383a17bd3543c151010168"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3151#issuecomment-2219004"}
